WEBVTT

00:41.640 --> 00:42.480
Sir.

00:44.120 --> 00:44.920
Sir!

00:45.520 --> 00:47.680
If banks are not granting a loan,

00:49.440 --> 00:52.480
we can ask Tata to fund us.

00:53.200 --> 00:55.320
When the investment
is on a large scale,

00:56.080 --> 00:58.280
no company takes the risk alone.

00:59.120 --> 01:03.480
Sir, what if we seek J.R.D.'s help?

01:04.640 --> 01:06.440
Banks will listen to him.

01:10.240 --> 01:12.800
We could try
some other venture, sir.

01:14.080 --> 01:15.400
He is right, sir.

01:16.080 --> 01:19.960
Banks have a problem
with watches, not with us.

01:21.120 --> 01:22.200
That's true.

01:23.080 --> 01:27.960
Mr. Desai, we've approached
most of the banks.

01:28.680 --> 01:29.880
So, where's the problem?

01:30.680 --> 01:33.480
The problem lies in our idea.

01:43.200 --> 01:45.160
If you don't believe
in the Watch Project,

01:46.520 --> 01:50.880
I'll make sure you all
find another job at Tata.

01:57.040 --> 01:58.160
I believe in it.

02:30.640 --> 02:32.200
How are you, Mr. Desai?

02:33.480 --> 02:34.560
Superb.

02:38.800 --> 02:39.600
Whoa!

02:46.400 --> 02:47.880
You might be a good liar,

02:48.760 --> 02:50.640
but your 'akuri'gives you away.

02:51.720 --> 02:52.880
What happened?

02:54.120 --> 02:55.680
Who gets a higher salary,

02:56.200 --> 02:58.240
a journalist or a detective?

02:59.080 --> 03:01.520
Because it's never too late
to change professions.

03:01.560 --> 03:02.960
In that case,
you should become a lawyer.

03:03.440 --> 03:05.000
You're very good
at dodging questions.

03:05.200 --> 03:06.800
And they even get paid more.

03:06.800 --> 03:07.680
Hmm.

03:14.840 --> 03:16.680
Now tell me. What happened?

03:18.840 --> 03:21.240
Titan's problems
just don't seem to end.

03:23.560 --> 03:25.520
I wanted to create a legacy project.

03:27.760 --> 03:29.560
Jeh trusted me with it.

03:31.800 --> 03:33.840
I could lose a mentor and a friend.

03:40.320 --> 03:42.800
No matter what happens,
I'm always with you.

03:44.600 --> 03:45.600
Will you give me a loan?

03:45.880 --> 03:48.320
Not a loan,
but I'll definitely support you.

03:48.360 --> 03:49.200
Hmm?

03:49.760 --> 03:51.360
It's far more precious than a loan.

04:02.960 --> 04:04.360
How could you eat this?

04:05.400 --> 04:06.320
I know.

04:10.400 --> 04:11.480
Should we go out for dinner?

04:11.520 --> 04:12.640
- I think so.
- Hmm.

04:22.760 --> 04:25.320
It seems you're carrying the
entire company on your back.

04:26.800 --> 04:28.160
You'll get a loan,

04:28.280 --> 04:29.400
but first, eat something.

04:29.440 --> 04:30.960
Didn't KBI grant a loan?

04:31.520 --> 04:34.280
How do you know about the
relationship between KBI and Tata?

04:34.720 --> 04:35.960
The whole world knows it.

04:36.800 --> 04:38.160
Did you try other banks?

04:38.480 --> 04:39.520
We tried them all.

04:39.640 --> 04:40.520
Canara Bank?

04:41.440 --> 04:43.800
Megha, I know the GM of Canara Bank.

04:44.400 --> 04:45.200
I'll talk to him.

04:45.560 --> 04:48.120
Canara Bank won't invest
in a project like ours.

04:48.360 --> 04:49.960
You can at least try.

04:50.600 --> 04:53.280
Tell me something.
Did you prepare a presentation?

04:53.480 --> 04:54.800
- Yes.
- Hmm.

04:55.040 --> 04:55.920
Let's hear it.

04:56.040 --> 04:57.880
Why? What will you do about it?

04:58.040 --> 05:01.480
Think of me as the bank's GM.

05:01.880 --> 05:03.560
Okay? Now start.

05:04.840 --> 05:05.760
Come on! Come on!

05:06.080 --> 05:07.200
Come on, let's hear it.

05:07.840 --> 05:09.280
Yes. Come on!

05:24.400 --> 05:27.520
Have you ever thought
that even though our country

05:27.720 --> 05:30.240
manufactures 1.8 million
watches every year,

05:30.280 --> 05:32.600
people still prefer
smuggled watches?

05:33.760 --> 05:34.600
For luxury?

05:35.920 --> 05:37.320
- The designs?
- Correct.

05:37.520 --> 05:38.760
But not entirely.

05:39.160 --> 05:42.680
These watches enhance
people's sense of self-worth.

05:43.040 --> 05:44.160
Those watches make them feel that,

05:44.160 --> 05:47.760
no matter how bad their time is,
they can always change it.

05:48.640 --> 05:49.560
Okay.

05:50.400 --> 05:52.720
But how will you compete with GMT?

05:53.040 --> 05:55.400
We don't want
to dominate GMT's market.

05:55.720 --> 05:56.840
Their customers are loyal,

05:56.840 --> 05:58.560
and they prefer mechanical watches.

05:58.720 --> 06:01.320
But mechanical watches are history,

06:01.360 --> 06:03.080
while quartz watches are the future.

06:03.280 --> 06:05.760
Now, what is quartz technology?

06:06.240 --> 06:08.400
A quartz crystal
generates vibrations

06:08.440 --> 06:11.280
when powered by a battery.

06:11.560 --> 06:13.360
It then sends these vibrations
to the divider circuit...

06:13.400 --> 06:14.440
Wait a minute!

06:14.720 --> 06:16.080
I'll explain in Hindi.

06:16.080 --> 06:17.800
No, language is not the problem.

06:18.640 --> 06:22.320
I'm no Einstein, Megha, so I
can't understand this technology.

06:23.120 --> 06:25.680
For now, I'm acting as the GM
who might grant you a loan.

06:25.880 --> 06:27.440
Yes, but if we don't explain,

06:27.480 --> 06:28.760
what about transparency?

06:28.800 --> 06:30.480
What you call transparency

06:30.480 --> 06:32.320
will only create confusion.

06:34.840 --> 06:35.680
See.

06:36.120 --> 06:38.920
Your presentation
may be technically correct,

06:39.800 --> 06:42.840
but your answer is preventing banks
from granting you a loan.

06:43.800 --> 06:45.680
They've failed to understand
this technology.

06:46.480 --> 06:47.520
Did you get it?

06:48.720 --> 06:50.080
What should our answer be then?

06:54.040 --> 06:56.720
Megha, are you sure
about this answer?

06:57.960 --> 06:59.000
Very sure, sir.

07:02.360 --> 07:04.800
Mr. Desai,
the GM will be here any moment.

07:05.040 --> 07:06.400
- Please go inside.
- Thank you.

07:25.360 --> 07:27.120
Quarterly report in two hours.

07:33.360 --> 07:34.160
Yes, please.

07:34.480 --> 07:36.840
Sir, this is our pitch document.

07:37.160 --> 07:38.880
Please take a look at this,

07:38.920 --> 07:42.280
and this is
the original loan application.

07:46.680 --> 07:47.560
Start the pitch.

07:59.920 --> 08:00.880
Ma'am, what's the time?

08:01.680 --> 08:04.840
This is Titan's vision.

08:09.240 --> 08:12.280
How will you compete
with a giant like GMT?

08:12.400 --> 08:13.760
We're not here to compete, sir.

08:14.400 --> 08:17.720
GMT's customers are loyal
to the mechanical watches.

08:18.040 --> 08:19.880
We're not targeting GMT's market.

08:20.440 --> 08:21.520
We want to create our own.

08:22.000 --> 08:23.280
With this quartz technology?

08:23.480 --> 08:24.280
Yes!

08:26.120 --> 08:27.080
Gentlemen,

08:27.720 --> 08:30.520
we don't understand
quartz technology.

08:31.040 --> 08:34.040
And it's difficult for us to invest
in something we don't understand.

08:34.360 --> 08:35.480
Absolutely.

08:35.560 --> 08:37.000
When we watch TV,

08:37.920 --> 08:40.360
we don't check the circuit diagram.

08:41.240 --> 08:42.880
We just know

08:43.160 --> 08:46.200
that the TV switches on
the moment we press the button.

08:46.760 --> 08:49.440
All we need to know
is that it's convenient.

08:49.960 --> 08:52.360
The quartz watches
are exactly like that.

08:53.000 --> 08:54.760
To add to that,

08:54.880 --> 08:57.840
winding mechanical watches

08:57.960 --> 08:59.680
tires people.

09:00.320 --> 09:03.320
However, if a watch is not wound,
time will stop.

09:03.640 --> 09:05.400
By contrast, time never stops

09:05.600 --> 09:08.520
in quartz watches.

09:11.680 --> 09:12.480
Really?

09:12.640 --> 09:14.600
It doesn't stop
for a couple of years.

09:15.480 --> 09:16.800
If it does stop,

09:18.240 --> 09:19.920
just change the battery
in five minutes

09:19.960 --> 09:21.360
and it starts working again.

09:21.680 --> 09:23.640
We'll provide a warranty.

09:24.400 --> 09:26.560
Even if I believe you,

09:28.200 --> 09:29.880
who will buy your watches?

09:31.240 --> 09:32.080
The whole world.

09:35.480 --> 09:37.280
Tata means trust,

09:38.320 --> 09:40.920
and Titan is a seed of Tata.

09:41.280 --> 09:43.800
It will grow with your help
and ours.

09:43.960 --> 09:45.040
I want people

09:45.800 --> 09:48.680
to visit our stores for Titan,

09:49.600 --> 09:50.840
not just for a watch.

09:51.280 --> 09:52.760
Because Titan holds a promise.

09:52.920 --> 09:55.040
The promise of joining
the Tata family.

09:55.800 --> 09:57.960
The promise of fine craftsmanship,

09:58.200 --> 10:00.320
elegance, reliability,

10:00.720 --> 10:02.160
and an enduring legacy.

10:02.600 --> 10:05.520
The promise that Titan
will not be just a watch.

10:06.600 --> 10:08.400
It could become
the identity of this country.

10:23.960 --> 10:25.080
What happened, sir?

10:27.720 --> 10:28.960
I suppose

10:30.480 --> 10:32.880
we'll have to find some land
to make watches.

10:37.760 --> 10:39.760
Your answer worked, Megha.

10:40.360 --> 10:41.480
Well done.

10:41.680 --> 10:43.960
- Thank you, sir!
- Now let's get the hell out of here

10:43.960 --> 10:45.160
before he changes his mind.

10:51.800 --> 10:52.840
Megha!

10:53.760 --> 10:54.720
Thank you!

10:56.480 --> 10:58.600
Oh! Congratulations!

10:59.240 --> 11:01.600
Why did you lie
about being an Arts professor?

11:01.760 --> 11:03.960
He's my brother, Devendra, not me.

11:04.600 --> 11:05.480
What?

11:05.600 --> 11:06.960
Didn't you watch 'Seeta Aur Geeta'?

11:07.440 --> 11:08.680
'Ram Aur Shyam'?

11:09.480 --> 11:10.880
He went for commerce,
while I chose the arts.

11:11.080 --> 11:11.880
So he...

11:11.880 --> 11:14.320
Yes! He's clean-shaven,
while I wear a moustache.

11:18.360 --> 11:21.280
Give me the 'laddus'
your mother made. Hand them to me!

11:22.040 --> 11:23.440
I'm making tea. Would you like some?

11:23.920 --> 11:25.320
Do you know how to make tea?

11:25.360 --> 11:26.720
My tea might boil over.

11:26.760 --> 11:28.440
Please come inside.
Let's sit and talk.

11:28.640 --> 11:30.000
Wonderful.

11:41.200 --> 11:43.560
Congratulations on the loan.

11:43.880 --> 11:45.160
Who told you?

11:46.080 --> 11:47.360
- Your 'akuri'.
- Aha!

11:47.400 --> 11:48.520
It's perfect.

11:50.440 --> 11:52.560
So, when are you
going to Tamil Nadu?

11:52.840 --> 11:53.800
Tomorrow morning.

11:54.280 --> 11:55.280
So soon?

11:55.520 --> 11:56.360
I know.

11:58.720 --> 12:00.080
- Packing?
- Done.

12:00.240 --> 12:01.320
Shyarsh and Honey helped me.

12:09.880 --> 12:13.960
Can you just... You're crowding the
man in the kitchen. Move a little.

12:14.960 --> 12:16.040
Thank you.

12:19.840 --> 12:20.960
Wine with lunch?

12:21.880 --> 12:22.800
Sure!

12:23.920 --> 12:25.040
I don't mind.

12:25.280 --> 12:26.440
I knew you wouldn't.

12:36.200 --> 12:38.200
So, where are we starting? Here?

12:38.680 --> 12:40.200
- Salem.
- Salem?

12:40.280 --> 12:41.520
- Salem.
- Salem.

12:47.000 --> 12:47.960
Perfect!

12:49.440 --> 12:50.320
Right?

12:50.960 --> 12:51.760
No.

12:52.080 --> 12:52.920
"No?"

12:53.560 --> 12:55.360
We aren't building
an open-air factory.

12:56.080 --> 12:57.680
The plant will be a closed space.

12:57.840 --> 13:00.480
Sir, the workers
will be constantly moving,

13:00.960 --> 13:03.560
so it will be
very difficult to avoid dust.

13:03.600 --> 13:05.360
Provide the workers

13:05.400 --> 13:07.760
with plastic shoe covers
when they enter the factory.

13:07.960 --> 13:09.720
And use a blower to remove dust
from their clothes. That's it.

13:09.760 --> 13:12.160
We'll have to do
all that anyway, Shankar.

13:12.520 --> 13:14.120
It would be better

13:14.560 --> 13:15.960
if we avoided the dust problem.

13:16.360 --> 13:17.440
Let's keep looking.

13:18.000 --> 13:19.240
- Right?
- Let's find another place, sir.

13:19.240 --> 13:20.160
Yes, let's go.

13:23.080 --> 13:24.080
Please come, sir.

13:32.400 --> 13:33.960
I'll come today, Kumud.

13:34.880 --> 13:35.880
Please don't worry.

13:36.320 --> 13:37.600
Okay? I'm coming.

13:39.240 --> 13:40.120
What happened?

13:41.760 --> 13:43.480
Dad went out this morning.

13:43.840 --> 13:44.680
Oh God!

13:44.680 --> 13:46.120
And he hasn’t returned yet.

13:48.440 --> 13:50.040
He must have lost his way back home.

13:50.640 --> 13:52.760
You should go.
I'll handle everything here.

14:05.640 --> 14:06.560
No, sir.

14:06.760 --> 14:08.360
The components will rust.

14:09.320 --> 14:11.840
'It's believed
we can find God Himself,'

14:13.360 --> 14:15.920
- 'yet we couldn't find suitable
land for the factory.'- No, sir.

14:16.960 --> 14:17.760
No!

14:18.120 --> 14:18.960
No!

14:19.120 --> 14:19.920
No!

14:19.960 --> 14:23.560
'Sometimes the problem was dust,
other times it was the moisture,'

14:24.880 --> 14:27.000
'and sometimes mosquitoes.'

14:36.200 --> 14:38.280
Sir, look at this section.

14:38.320 --> 14:39.680
- Hmm.
- This is good for us.

14:40.760 --> 14:42.400
He's 'paithyam'.

14:43.320 --> 14:44.720
What's 'paithyam'?

14:44.760 --> 14:46.360
Sir, let it be. Forget it.

14:46.880 --> 14:49.240
The one it was meant for understood.

14:59.920 --> 15:02.520
I showed you all the plots
I knew about,

15:03.480 --> 15:05.840
but your favourite engineer
didn't like a single one.

15:06.280 --> 15:07.800
Let's not compromise, Shankar.

15:08.520 --> 15:09.600
Let's find the best.

15:10.560 --> 15:13.200
Huh? What do you think, 'paithyam'?

15:21.360 --> 15:23.360
It's hot. Just be careful.

15:27.600 --> 15:28.400
Hello.

15:28.440 --> 15:29.280
Did you find Uncle?

15:29.440 --> 15:30.640
Yes, I found him.

15:30.880 --> 15:32.160
He had veered off to New Bombay,

15:32.680 --> 15:34.280
but by God's grace, he's safe.

15:34.920 --> 15:35.920
Good.

15:36.680 --> 15:38.680
I'll come there tomorrow.

15:39.080 --> 15:40.160
Okay. Okay.

15:40.880 --> 15:42.520
Okay, thank you. Thank you, Akash.

15:42.720 --> 15:44.320
- Take care, my friend.
- 'Yes!'

15:44.800 --> 15:46.200
- Okay, bye.
- 'Bye.'

15:55.560 --> 15:56.560
[in Tamil] Please stop!

15:59.400 --> 16:00.720
Do you want to pee?

16:01.840 --> 16:04.720
Did you learn Tamil
while searching for land?

16:04.760 --> 16:07.040
No, sir. I'm from IIT Madras.

16:11.120 --> 16:12.440
- This side.
- Uh...

16:30.880 --> 16:32.200
[in Tamil] This is it, sir!

16:32.680 --> 16:34.680
- What do you mean?
- It's perfect.

16:34.960 --> 16:36.720
- Moisture? - [in Tamil] None!

16:36.960 --> 16:38.000
- Insects? - [in Tamil] None!

16:38.040 --> 16:39.120
- Dust?
- [in Tamil] None!

16:39.720 --> 16:41.280
Can we manufacture watches here?

16:41.320 --> 16:42.160
[in Tamil] No!

16:42.600 --> 16:43.760
- Huh?
- Why?

16:44.760 --> 16:46.240
Is this plot not government-owned?

16:46.920 --> 16:47.960
- It is.
- So?

16:49.040 --> 16:51.040
This lies on the border
of Tamil Nadu and Karnataka.

16:51.160 --> 16:51.960
I know.

16:51.960 --> 16:53.280
If you build a plant here,

16:53.440 --> 16:55.320
our neighbours
will be employed here.

16:55.560 --> 16:56.360
No!

16:56.400 --> 16:57.400
- Hear us out.
- Uh...

16:57.800 --> 16:58.800
- Shankar!
- No.

16:58.920 --> 17:00.080
- Shankar!
- Sir!

17:00.200 --> 17:01.960
This is the perfect place for Titan.

17:02.080 --> 17:02.880
Yes!

17:02.920 --> 17:03.800
And why is that?

17:03.920 --> 17:05.920
Because we're just one hour away
from Bangalore.

17:05.960 --> 17:07.120
What's so special about Bangalore?

17:07.160 --> 17:08.760
Our competitor, GMT, is based there.

17:08.800 --> 17:10.440
And what about employment?

17:10.680 --> 17:13.400
Employment will be offered
exclusively to Tamil Nadu residents.

17:13.480 --> 17:16.560
- Yes! - I swear
on the future of Titan, Shankar!

17:17.600 --> 17:18.400
No.

17:18.480 --> 17:19.600
- Sir.
- Huh.

17:20.600 --> 17:21.840
Shankar, say "seri".

17:22.320 --> 17:23.200
Shankar.

17:23.480 --> 17:24.600
Come on, say "seri".

17:24.640 --> 17:25.840
- Come on, say it.
- Don't... Don't do this.

17:26.000 --> 17:27.800
- Please!
- We won't find a better place, sir.

17:27.800 --> 17:29.760
- Shankar, say "seri".
- This place is perfect.

17:30.080 --> 17:30.880
What?

17:30.920 --> 17:32.080
Say "seri", Shankar.

17:33.080 --> 17:34.720
- Promise?
- Promise!

17:36.080 --> 17:37.360
- [in Tamil] 'Seri'?
- 'Seri'!

17:38.160 --> 17:39.200
- [in Tamil] Okay.
- 'Seri'!

17:39.880 --> 17:41.320
- Woo-hoo!
- Wonderful!

17:41.400 --> 17:42.960
I'm proud of you.

17:46.040 --> 17:47.080
I love you!

17:47.120 --> 17:48.040
Well done!

18:09.720 --> 18:11.560
"I offer You!"

18:12.400 --> 18:14.840
So, you found a place
for your factory near GMT?

18:15.240 --> 18:17.760
Well, a very wise

18:17.960 --> 18:19.480
and fussy man once said

18:19.880 --> 18:21.400
that if you want to run a business,

18:21.480 --> 18:22.760
you must have courage

18:23.560 --> 18:26.520
- and keep an eye
on your competitors. - Yes.

18:26.560 --> 18:27.840
He was absolutely right.

18:29.280 --> 18:31.120
So, how do you intend to apply it?

18:31.560 --> 18:33.360
We'll apply it, sir.

18:35.800 --> 18:36.720
Look at this.

18:36.840 --> 18:38.600
We are going to make Titan fly.

18:39.360 --> 18:40.680
- "Fly?"
- Hmm!

18:41.760 --> 18:44.880
Do you know the share price of GMT?

18:47.600 --> 18:49.480
Uh, yes...

18:50.760 --> 18:53.000
It's fifty rupees. What about it?

18:53.560 --> 18:56.640
It took GMT 30 years
to reach a share price of Rs. 50,

18:56.640 --> 18:58.720
and you haven't even
started making watches yet.

19:00.600 --> 19:03.680
By the way,
the time you asked for is over.

19:04.560 --> 19:06.400
Now, whenever the watch is built,

19:07.800 --> 19:09.160
it will already be late.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.520
I understand. Yes, sir.

19:51.880 --> 19:52.840
Nice party.

19:53.240 --> 19:55.640
GMT is laying off
many workers next month.

19:55.960 --> 19:57.360
I've offered him a job at Titan.

19:59.680 --> 20:00.960
- Hi!
- Hello.

20:01.680 --> 20:03.080
I'm Ravi from GMT.

20:03.320 --> 20:04.360
- Hello, Ravi.
- Hello.

20:05.160 --> 20:07.920
Let me introduce you
to Sameer Reddy.

20:09.280 --> 20:11.080
- The man in red cheques?
- Yes, you're right.

20:11.360 --> 20:14.120
He has been working in the R&D
department at GMT for 22 years.

20:14.520 --> 20:17.240
He's the kind of man who has
twenty solutions to every problem.

20:17.320 --> 20:18.240
Oh.

20:18.960 --> 20:21.600
His experience speaks
louder than words.

20:22.360 --> 20:26.200
But he gets exhausted
by constant delays.

20:26.640 --> 20:27.520
Ah.

20:29.560 --> 20:30.680
Ms. Pooja!

20:31.640 --> 20:34.120
She's a horologist
and a mathematical genius.

20:34.720 --> 20:37.000
If a watch is running
one second slow,

20:37.040 --> 20:38.520
she can tell you
exactly what time it will show

20:38.760 --> 20:40.400
at this exact moment next year.

20:40.920 --> 20:42.640
She's in a high position,

20:43.040 --> 20:44.720
but her pay cheque
is still eight years old.

20:44.720 --> 20:45.560
Why so?

20:45.560 --> 20:47.120
Because GMT is overstaffed.

20:47.480 --> 20:48.960
When the population is high,

20:49.120 --> 20:51.400
per capita income decreases, sir.

20:51.800 --> 20:52.640
Hmm.

20:52.720 --> 20:54.080
The star of the show...

20:56.320 --> 20:58.040
Mr. A.J.K.

20:58.360 --> 20:59.960
He's the head
of the manufacturing department.

21:00.280 --> 21:02.800
If GMT is still running,
it's only because of him.

21:03.200 --> 21:04.720
For the past two years,
they've been submitting

21:04.800 --> 21:06.480
a requisition for a machine
to senior management,

21:06.920 --> 21:08.480
but none of them has responded.

21:08.680 --> 21:11.400
And this has been happening
for the past fifteen years.

21:11.720 --> 21:14.680
- Then we should help them.
- Hmm.

21:15.360 --> 21:16.640
- Yes, sure.
- Sure?

21:16.840 --> 21:18.600
- Sure? - Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

21:19.080 --> 21:20.960
Let's play a game of musical chairs.

21:21.000 --> 21:22.760
Let’s have some fun. Please join us.

21:22.800 --> 21:23.640
Please come.

21:24.120 --> 21:25.320
Please come.

21:35.280 --> 21:37.600
- Excuse me.
- Sure.

21:51.960 --> 21:53.160
Gaurav, it's you!

21:54.080 --> 21:55.120
Akash!

21:55.760 --> 21:56.680
How are you?

21:57.040 --> 21:58.880
I was fine until now,

21:59.120 --> 22:00.880
but after what I heard today,
I am not.

22:17.800 --> 22:18.600
Oh!

22:18.760 --> 22:21.240
- Oh!
- Boo!

22:25.160 --> 22:26.760
So, what happened to you?

22:27.400 --> 22:28.320
Titan.

22:29.960 --> 22:33.840
Are you talking about that
new business that's just started?

22:34.040 --> 22:37.040
A business is never new.
It's the technology that's new.

22:38.120 --> 22:40.040
After seeing their technology,

22:40.120 --> 22:41.840
your heart will skip a beat.

22:57.080 --> 22:57.960
Whoa!

22:59.040 --> 23:00.080
Oh, no!

23:00.160 --> 23:01.520
You’ve stolen the show!

23:03.840 --> 23:04.760
Hmm.

23:05.760 --> 23:06.760
What kind of technology?

23:07.000 --> 23:07.840
It's their machines.

23:09.360 --> 23:10.480
Their machines are so advanced

23:10.520 --> 23:12.640
that even Swiss brands
pale in comparison.

23:13.080 --> 23:14.960
Now you're exaggerating.

23:15.320 --> 23:17.080
What machines
could Titan possibly have?

23:17.200 --> 23:19.640
If you don't believe me,
it's your loss.

23:33.960 --> 23:34.840
Hey!

23:35.200 --> 23:36.200
Oh, no!

23:36.480 --> 23:38.320
- Oh!
- Very well played.

23:41.880 --> 23:43.560
Titan may have new machines,

23:43.720 --> 23:46.360
but they don’t have
the experience that GMT possesses.

23:46.640 --> 23:48.040
They're the Tatas.

23:48.400 --> 23:49.560
They can do anything.

23:51.800 --> 23:53.480
Our collaborator is Citizen.

23:54.320 --> 23:55.760
I don't think Titan can compete.

23:55.840 --> 23:58.360
Do visit us at Titan sometime.

23:58.400 --> 23:59.440
I mean...

23:59.520 --> 24:01.080
Please do... Do visit them.

24:02.000 --> 24:05.960
You'll be proud to be
a 'Citizen'of this country.

24:25.120 --> 24:26.680
I took it. Please leave.

24:27.240 --> 24:28.040
Oh!

24:28.240 --> 24:30.160
- Well played, Akash.
- Well played.

24:31.280 --> 24:33.200
Quite an impressive performance.

24:34.800 --> 24:35.960
Thank you.

24:37.800 --> 24:38.760
Shall we go out for dinner?

24:39.200 --> 24:40.000
Huh?

24:42.880 --> 24:45.240
I mean, the dinner must be ready.

24:47.160 --> 24:48.280
We'll go there in a while.

24:58.200 --> 24:59.360
- Whoa!
- Hey!

25:00.840 --> 25:02.960
Well, it was lovely meeting you.

25:03.000 --> 25:04.840
- Yes. Akash.
- A.J.K.

25:05.600 --> 25:06.560
Hi, I'm Akash.

25:07.240 --> 25:08.120
- Hello!
- Hi!

25:08.120 --> 25:09.080
- I'm Akash.
- Sameer.

25:11.320 --> 25:13.680
Whatever you just said,
is it all true?

25:13.720 --> 25:14.920
Well,

25:15.920 --> 25:17.200
you can come and see for yourself.

25:20.200 --> 25:21.280
Are you from Titan?

25:23.520 --> 25:27.560
At 10 a.m. tomorrow, a car will come
to pick you up. Well played.

25:29.160 --> 25:30.560
- Come on.
- See you tomorrow.

25:30.960 --> 25:31.960
10 a.m.!

25:32.360 --> 25:33.400
Well played, sir.

25:57.520 --> 26:00.400
You spoke about
the big Swiss machines at Titan.

26:02.360 --> 26:03.960
But we can't see them.

26:04.760 --> 26:09.120
We agree, but to make Titan
extraordinary, we need your help.

26:09.200 --> 26:11.360
We're not interested in leaving
a secure government job

26:11.480 --> 26:14.880
to join a semi-private company.

26:15.160 --> 26:16.840
Because if Titan fails,

26:17.080 --> 26:19.080
it would be just a minor
setback for the Tatas,

26:19.240 --> 26:21.280
but for us, it would mean
the end of our careers.

26:21.800 --> 26:24.360
So, thank you for the offer.

26:25.400 --> 26:27.200
- Ma'am! Ma'am, please...
- Wait a minute.

26:28.760 --> 26:31.520
Why are "ebauche unit",

26:31.880 --> 26:34.600
"gears unit" and
"movement unit" written here?

26:35.360 --> 26:36.520
Vendors supply these, don't they?

26:37.320 --> 26:38.920
Ordinarily, yes.

26:38.920 --> 26:39.920
'Samanyaroop'.

26:39.920 --> 26:41.320
Normally, yes.

26:41.480 --> 26:42.720
Titan's dream

26:43.960 --> 26:45.960
is to make "Made in India" watches.

26:48.600 --> 26:51.480
For that,
you'll need a lot of machines.

26:51.840 --> 26:52.800
Yes.

26:53.080 --> 26:54.200
Where will you bring them from?

26:54.320 --> 26:55.960
Write the names on the board,

26:56.560 --> 26:57.720
and we'll buy those machines.

26:59.120 --> 27:00.080
I'm sorry, sir.

27:00.560 --> 27:02.080
It's not a restaurant where we can

27:02.440 --> 27:04.000
simply place an order
and get the food served.

27:05.160 --> 27:07.360
If we place the order
for machines today,

27:07.840 --> 27:10.600
it will take years
just for it to be accepted.

27:11.320 --> 27:13.160
What machine

27:13.680 --> 27:16.320
did you request

27:17.040 --> 27:19.320
from GMT two years ago?

27:20.920 --> 27:22.200
Boring milling machine, sir.

27:22.360 --> 27:25.120
Boring milling machine! That was it.

27:26.120 --> 27:27.200
Sir, is this the one?

27:36.760 --> 27:37.680
Approved!

27:38.600 --> 27:39.880
Your machine will be delivered.

27:40.560 --> 27:41.720
We here at Titan

27:42.320 --> 27:45.320
believe that if we invest
in the right people,

27:45.920 --> 27:48.840
they will ensure we invest
in the right components.

27:52.160 --> 27:54.680
Write down your requirements
on the board,

27:55.440 --> 27:56.760
and we'll arrange for those machines

27:57.480 --> 27:59.120
within a month.

28:22.760 --> 28:25.240
If you can get these machines
within a month,

28:25.440 --> 28:28.400
we will resign from GMT

28:28.960 --> 28:30.040
and join this company.

28:32.080 --> 28:33.080
Fantastic!

28:33.240 --> 28:35.200
Today is the 26th.

28:35.440 --> 28:37.760
Please be ready
with your resignation letters

28:38.640 --> 28:40.160
by the 26th next month.

28:50.400 --> 28:51.400
Thank you for coming.

28:57.080 --> 28:59.320
[in Tamil] All of you, please come!

28:59.680 --> 29:00.760
Everyone, please come!

29:01.360 --> 29:04.960
Those seeking employment,
please come!

29:11.360 --> 29:13.240
Tata is offering jobs!

29:16.480 --> 29:18.440
Anyone seeking employment,
please come!

29:18.480 --> 29:20.160
Do come! Please come!

29:25.080 --> 29:26.960
This is a golden opportunity.

29:27.000 --> 29:29.840
You're invited!

29:29.840 --> 29:32.040
Everyone is invited!
Don't miss this chance!

29:32.080 --> 29:33.880
Everyone is invited! Please come!

30:07.960 --> 30:09.960
[in Tamil] He's Josh.

30:10.400 --> 30:13.520
He will train you in watchmaking.

30:14.080 --> 30:17.040
He has come from abroad.

30:18.200 --> 30:20.720
[in Tamil]
Are you all ready for the exam?

30:20.840 --> 30:21.880
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

30:31.320 --> 30:34.040
Why don't we choose engineers

30:34.960 --> 30:36.760
or degree holders
for these positions?

30:36.960 --> 30:39.840
Do they need to be
engineers or degree holders?

30:41.560 --> 30:43.040
They are blank slates

30:43.440 --> 30:46.120
and will learn and adapt
very quickly, I assure you.

30:47.320 --> 30:50.680
But we could choose
students from the cities.

30:50.840 --> 30:53.200
All these people are villagers.

30:54.960 --> 30:55.760
Yes, they are...

30:56.560 --> 30:57.960
They are the roots of this country.

30:58.760 --> 31:03.000
This factory shouldn't be
just about Titan and profits.

31:03.720 --> 31:07.160
Ideally, we should empower
everyone around us.

31:11.040 --> 31:11.880
Yes.

31:14.960 --> 31:16.040
- Sir.
- Hmm?

31:16.240 --> 31:18.240
The announcement was for everyone,

31:18.240 --> 31:20.280
so why did only male students come?

31:24.720 --> 31:26.040
[in Tamil]
Attention! Attention! Attention!

31:26.040 --> 31:27.360
Titan invites you!
Attention, please!

31:27.400 --> 31:30.360
We are hiring not just men
but women too!

31:36.320 --> 31:38.000
[in Tamil] Attention, please!

31:38.720 --> 31:40.840
We are hiring both men and women!

31:45.280 --> 31:46.080
Gaurav, please.

31:46.080 --> 31:47.600
Can we stop somewhere?
I'm so hungry.

31:48.440 --> 31:49.520
Oh, okay.

31:52.880 --> 31:54.800
Just give me a minute.

31:55.680 --> 31:57.520
- [in Tamil] Greetings!
- Greetings!

31:58.480 --> 32:01.160
[in Tamil]
Is there a restaurant nearby?

32:01.360 --> 32:04.760
No, there's no restaurant
within 20 kilometres.

32:05.960 --> 32:07.120
Are you hungry?

32:07.680 --> 32:08.960
[in Tamil] Yes, he's hungry.

32:09.680 --> 32:11.760
Oh, please come home
with me for a meal.

32:11.840 --> 32:13.880
- [in Tamil] Thank you very much.
- Please do come.

32:14.200 --> 32:16.280
Josh! Take your shoes off.

32:29.520 --> 32:30.600
What's this?

32:30.800 --> 32:31.880
It's idli sambar.

32:32.160 --> 32:34.200
It's one
of my favourite dishes ever.

32:35.240 --> 32:36.800
- Shall we wash hands?
- Yes.

32:37.160 --> 32:38.760
[in Tamil]
Can we wash our hands here?

32:38.840 --> 32:40.200
- Shall we wash hands?
- Yes.

32:50.280 --> 32:51.600
Josh... Josh.

32:52.640 --> 32:53.840
What's she doing?

32:56.360 --> 32:59.640
She's cleaning the impurities
from the pulses.

33:02.280 --> 33:04.160
Eureka! I found it.

33:06.200 --> 33:07.320
Congratulations!

33:07.440 --> 33:09.040
You've just secured a job.

33:15.320 --> 33:16.320
Congratulations!

33:46.480 --> 33:48.280
'Finally, out of thousands,'

33:48.280 --> 33:50.800
'97 girls and 3 boys were selected'

33:51.720 --> 33:52.680
'to make watches.'

33:53.680 --> 33:54.560
Welcome, girls.

33:54.720 --> 33:57.600
'But they were completely
unaware of the challenges ahead.'

33:57.920 --> 33:59.760
Boys, please have a seat.

34:01.280 --> 34:03.640
[in Tamil] Greetings, all.
Please be seated.

34:06.000 --> 34:08.640
Here are some needles and thread.
Please collect them.

34:09.440 --> 34:12.360
[in Tamil] It contains needles
and thread. Please take them.

34:19.400 --> 34:20.240
Ready?

34:24.880 --> 34:25.920
Start!

34:26.200 --> 34:27.160
Stop!

34:30.400 --> 34:31.240
What's happened?

34:31.640 --> 34:32.560
Anyone?

34:33.840 --> 34:35.840
It's been just one second, Josh.

34:36.800 --> 34:37.720
So?

34:38.320 --> 34:39.320
Okay.

34:42.560 --> 34:43.600
[in Tamil] Keep on trying.

34:44.280 --> 34:45.640
Ready? Start!

34:46.400 --> 34:47.320
Stop!

34:48.120 --> 34:49.160
Ready?

34:49.600 --> 34:50.520
Start!

34:50.960 --> 34:51.840
Stop!

34:53.160 --> 34:54.120
Ready?

34:54.440 --> 34:55.960
Start! Stop!

34:57.480 --> 34:58.360
Ready?

34:58.600 --> 35:00.560
Start! Stop!

35:00.560 --> 35:02.440
Start! Stop!

35:02.960 --> 35:04.800
Start! Stop!

35:05.520 --> 35:07.080
Start! Stop!

35:07.680 --> 35:09.240
Start! Stop!

35:09.680 --> 35:11.200
Start! Stop!

35:12.240 --> 35:13.080
Start!

35:13.480 --> 35:14.400
Stop!

35:17.320 --> 35:18.520
Is he still playing midfield?

35:20.360 --> 35:21.800
Is he now a striker?

35:23.800 --> 35:26.320
I can't wait to come back
and congratulate him.

35:26.680 --> 35:28.120
I want to celebrate soon.

35:29.680 --> 35:31.120
Okay, fine.

35:31.520 --> 35:32.640
Good night, darling.

35:34.160 --> 35:35.360
Good night.

35:38.440 --> 35:40.760
[in Tamil] Oi, listen!
Please have a look!

35:42.680 --> 35:44.040
[in Tamil]
Would you like a cup of coffee?

35:45.440 --> 35:46.800
- [in Tamil] Oi!
- Hear us out!

35:55.000 --> 35:55.920
Ready?

35:57.480 --> 35:58.800
Start! Stop!

35:59.880 --> 36:01.320
Start! Stop!

36:04.080 --> 36:05.120
Very good.

36:07.160 --> 36:07.960
Done?

36:08.280 --> 36:09.240
Well done.

36:10.320 --> 36:12.360
Please reiterate to the engineers

36:12.760 --> 36:14.280
that the teeth can't vary.

36:14.480 --> 36:16.280
4.2020, plus or minus 10.

36:16.280 --> 36:18.160
Absolutely,
it's critical to quality.

36:18.640 --> 36:19.640
Sir.

36:20.280 --> 36:21.200
Come in.

36:29.960 --> 36:31.040
Sir...

36:33.600 --> 36:34.560
What happened?

36:35.200 --> 36:36.280
Is everything okay?

36:38.600 --> 36:39.800
Sir, um...

36:46.160 --> 36:47.960
- [in Tamil] Look at them!
- Would you like some coffee?

36:47.960 --> 36:50.960
- [in Tamil] Please hear us out!
- Come with us.

37:08.520 --> 37:10.360
This is the inside of our watch.

37:12.080 --> 37:14.120
This is the quartz crystal.

37:14.400 --> 37:18.680
The quartz crystal vibrates
32,000 times per second.

37:20.840 --> 37:22.280
It's the hero of our watch.

37:29.120 --> 37:29.920
What is it?

37:31.200 --> 37:32.040
It's nothing.

37:34.320 --> 37:36.000
How's everything with Josh?

37:37.360 --> 37:38.320
It's good.

37:38.840 --> 37:40.720
He asks for idli and sambar
every three hours.

37:43.400 --> 37:45.800
Boys and girls, I have
another test for you.

37:46.560 --> 37:47.480
Yet another task!

37:51.120 --> 37:52.320
Oh! It's easy!

37:53.840 --> 37:54.800
No! No! No!

37:54.840 --> 37:56.440
You have to do it like this.

38:05.040 --> 38:05.920
Fill it.

38:06.760 --> 38:08.680
Not a single seed should fall.

38:09.760 --> 38:11.720
[in Tamil]
Not a single seed should fall.

38:50.680 --> 38:52.560
Xerxes sent the taxi
especially for you.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.320
It's the 26th today.

39:00.240 --> 39:01.160
Please come.

39:01.560 --> 39:02.520
Please!

39:17.000 --> 39:17.920
- Sir.
- Hmm?

39:19.360 --> 39:20.960
- They are here.
- Here they are.

39:41.320 --> 39:42.480
I hope we delivered.

39:42.760 --> 39:43.760
As promised.

39:48.440 --> 39:49.960
I'll take that as a yes.

39:51.040 --> 39:51.880
Hello.

39:52.840 --> 39:54.120
It's lovely to have you here.

39:55.640 --> 39:57.240
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

39:58.920 --> 40:00.880
- Good to have you on board.
- Thank you.

40:03.480 --> 40:05.440
You're in the watchmaking business,

40:05.720 --> 40:08.200
but surprisingly,
you don't wear watches.

40:08.480 --> 40:09.400
Why is that?

40:09.960 --> 40:11.520
- Uh...
- We have decided

40:12.240 --> 40:15.360
not to wear watches
until we make one.

40:31.880 --> 40:33.720
Welcome to the world of Titan.

40:36.560 --> 40:37.760
I'm a horologist.

40:38.160 --> 40:39.800
If I take off my watch,

40:40.080 --> 40:41.680
it'll be bad for everyone.

40:41.960 --> 40:43.040
No... No.

40:43.080 --> 40:44.440
It's not a requirement.

40:45.640 --> 40:48.160
Anyway, let's meet
in my office after lunch.

40:48.400 --> 40:49.600
- Yes?
- Okay.

40:50.760 --> 40:51.680
- Okay?
- Thanks.

40:51.720 --> 40:53.080
- Looking forward.
- Same here.

40:54.280 --> 40:55.400
Shall I show you
the assembly section?

40:55.800 --> 40:56.760
Please come.

41:21.240 --> 41:22.160
Done?

41:25.560 --> 41:26.520
Well done!

41:26.840 --> 41:28.480
It's time for a new task.

41:29.080 --> 41:30.440
[in Tamil] All the best!

41:30.520 --> 41:31.600
Yet another task.

41:34.360 --> 41:35.360
Uh-uh!

41:45.400 --> 41:46.920
Let's assemble a watch.

42:21.240 --> 42:25.400
Your role as the Operations
Manager is now very important.

42:25.440 --> 42:26.600
Hmm. Sure, sir.

42:26.640 --> 42:27.840
You need to go to Japan,

42:27.880 --> 42:31.040
inspect the watch components there,
and book the shipment.

42:59.200 --> 43:01.040
Who sends you so many letters?

43:01.240 --> 43:03.040
I hope you don't mind sharing.

43:03.640 --> 43:04.680
They are from my mother, sir.

43:04.680 --> 43:07.200
Huh!
She can talk to you on the phone.

43:08.080 --> 43:10.440
She sends me photos
of potential grooms.

43:10.680 --> 43:11.880
Oh!

43:15.000 --> 43:17.320
All the best, Ms. Megha.

43:51.760 --> 43:53.840
- Sir!
- It takes over.

43:53.880 --> 43:54.720
Sir...

43:54.760 --> 43:56.120
- What's the matter?
- Sir.

43:56.680 --> 43:58.480
- Hello, Vijay!
- Sir, please have some sweets.

43:59.240 --> 44:00.040
For what?

44:00.240 --> 44:01.640
My wife is pregnant, sir.

44:01.680 --> 44:03.560
- Wow! Congratulations!
- "Wife?"

44:03.600 --> 44:04.760
When did you get married?

44:04.960 --> 44:06.240
It's been two years, Zee.

44:06.320 --> 44:07.320
Oh!

44:07.760 --> 44:08.880
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, sir.

44:08.960 --> 44:11.400
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations!

44:26.160 --> 44:27.640
- Sir, are you sure?
- Yes.

46:34.120 --> 46:36.160
This is what we call
a flying saucer test.

46:37.640 --> 46:38.480
Passed.

46:39.200 --> 46:40.120
It's working.

46:48.640 --> 46:49.960
Bastard!

46:50.080 --> 46:52.320
- Scoundrel!
- Sir, the watch...

46:55.680 --> 46:56.960
Hello, Jeh! No.

46:57.520 --> 46:59.720
Hey, Pinks. Where's Jeh?

46:59.960 --> 47:02.200
He's going to Delhi
today for an event.

47:02.280 --> 47:03.920
Oh, no. Okay.

47:04.320 --> 47:05.720
And don't call me Pinks.

47:06.560 --> 47:08.200
Okay. Thanks, Pinks.

47:30.800 --> 47:32.200
These are mustard seeds.

47:33.760 --> 47:35.640
Wow, it's amazing.

47:39.280 --> 47:40.400
Sir.

47:44.560 --> 47:46.360
Here are some idli and chutney

47:47.160 --> 47:48.880
for a safe and happy journey.

47:53.200 --> 47:54.320
Thank you so much

47:55.680 --> 47:56.960
for everything.

48:00.000 --> 48:01.160
Thank you. Uh-uh!

48:03.400 --> 48:04.560
Thank you! Thank you!

48:04.960 --> 48:06.160
Thank you.

48:10.840 --> 48:12.040
I will miss you all.

48:38.720 --> 48:39.840
Hello, Thelma!

48:40.160 --> 48:42.360
- Wow! How are you?
- I'm good.

48:42.440 --> 48:43.960
- Hello, Zee.
- Hi, Jeh.

48:44.040 --> 48:45.640
I wish we could have welcomed you,

48:45.760 --> 48:47.560
but we're going to a party.

48:48.280 --> 48:49.880
- This is good.
- He won't mind.

48:49.920 --> 48:50.760
He won't mind.

48:50.840 --> 48:53.640
How come you're here at this hour?

49:13.920 --> 49:14.880
My God.

49:25.840 --> 49:29.160
You've done it, Zee!

49:34.320 --> 49:35.360
Oh boy!

49:35.440 --> 49:37.200
You've done it!

49:38.320 --> 49:39.800
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, Jeh.

49:41.960 --> 49:44.160
I couldn't have asked
for a better day

49:44.920 --> 49:46.360
to receive this watch.

49:46.760 --> 49:49.440
Let's meet for breakfast tomorrow
morning at Bombay House.

49:50.680 --> 49:52.320
Bring your entire team.

49:53.520 --> 49:54.840
Congratulations!

49:55.600 --> 49:56.560
Thank you, Jeh!

50:04.400 --> 50:05.960
How long will you be in India?

50:07.520 --> 50:08.440
For two more days.

50:08.480 --> 50:10.400
Just two more days,

50:10.400 --> 50:13.120
but it's quality time.

50:14.000 --> 50:14.840
Right.

50:14.880 --> 50:16.800
How's the Watch Project going,
Mr. Tata?

50:16.960 --> 50:18.720
Oh, it's going very well indeed.

50:19.560 --> 50:20.360
Here!

50:20.680 --> 50:21.680
Ooh!

50:21.920 --> 50:23.080
Congratulations!

50:23.920 --> 50:25.560
It seems that only the Tatas

50:26.320 --> 50:27.920
are enjoying good days
and good times.

50:28.040 --> 50:29.760
I mean, it's beautiful.

50:30.720 --> 50:33.920
Good days don't just happen,
you have to make them happen.

50:34.920 --> 50:37.040
- It's been a long time, Mr. Tata.
- Oh!

50:37.040 --> 50:39.200
Hello, Mr. Jeuba!
It's so nice to see you again.

50:39.200 --> 50:40.320
Nice to see you.

50:40.520 --> 50:41.800
Let me introduce Kate.

50:41.880 --> 50:42.960
How do you do?

50:43.200 --> 50:45.000
- Hello, ma'am!
- This is my wife, Thelma.

50:45.160 --> 50:46.440
Nice meeting you too.

50:46.560 --> 50:47.800
- Hello.
- Gentlemen!

50:47.880 --> 50:48.800
Hello.
